   and 
  
    
      
        
          Y
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathbf {Y} }
   are jointly normally distributed,

  
    
      
        
          X
        
        ,
        
          Y
        
        ∼
         
        
          
            N
          
        
        (
        
          μ
        
        ,
        
          
            Σ
          
        
        )
        ,
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathbf {X} ,\mathbf {Y} \sim \ {\mathcal {N}}(\mathbf {\mu } ,\operatorname {\mathbf {\Sigma } } ),}
  then the conditional distribution for 
  
    
      
        
          Y
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathbf {Y} }
   given 
  
    
      
        
          X
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathbf {X} }
   is given by

  
    
      
        
          Y
        
        ∣
        
          X
        
